<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="standard-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" author="Kieran O'Donnell" dateTime="2021-03-29T09:10:48" id="_d9d7c3d5-1474-4b53-8335-c6691c21bd47" outputclass="standard-clause" type="insert"><sptc>3.1</sptc><title id="_f798cfde-4c77-46eb-aee2-c9b0c9a04d70">Clear opening width</title><p>Internal doorways must provide a minimum clear opening width of 820 mm, measured in accordance with <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/5017_0.14.0.xml#_4d085d33-a969-483a-bd8b-382b64f1c79c" id="_a5539deb-459b-4e46-a84e-c54ee93edc65" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 2.1</xref>.</p><callout id="_97f1a94e-d27a-4c6c-9c5e-fd697288959e"><callout-type info-type="application"/><p>Clause 3.1 only applies to a doorway that connects to, or is in the path of travel to, any of the following:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_0ae595ed-22bd-4955-8543-f9bc047a27f2"><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1326_0.4.0.xml#_b8eec66f-9c05-425d-8474-e6a2dfc2c0f4" id="_b6fcf671-f4f9-4b4c-b4f7-93d244622e37" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Habitable room</xref> or laundry on the ground or entry level.</li><li id="_d062bdf3-6133-4621-acae-84e3fe6d906e">Attached Class 10a garage or carport that forms part of an access path required by <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/4994_0.31.0.xml#_520db1d9-a633-4ac9-8c88-a960a99371f2" id="_2d10f1d2-a0cf-4dd8-a7be-b81ecdfb572a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-clause">Clause 1.1</xref>.</li><li id="_c8823b39-6edb-4ff1-bca2-fcc9d891e3eb"><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1445_0.13.0.xml#_3c082f1b-1601-4152-a723-dd1cbf1d71f9" id="_3dfad859-b082-4e40-8493-fce8c7a2fe4d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">Sanitary compartment</xref> on the ground or entry level complying with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/5057_0.6.0.xml#_0ed515fd-e288-4727-a377-0a19f9db35eb" id="_dd035427-f545-4d92-a17f-183c577313d3" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Parts 4</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/5059_0.7.0.xml#_917f49e9-bbf2-40a3-848a-2c3aea0c2c0d" id="_08b47007-b6bf-4261-b796-38b602a61ac6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">6</xref>.</li><li id="_38700243-5853-4373-baa4-a3d2d44f827a">Room containing a shower complying with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/5058_0.6.0.xml#_97ff85db-7076-4b5f-a13d-cd98225b0a52" id="_6f3b3fa2-8e13-4d61-ad4b-5a88fc11c09f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Parts 5</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/5059_0.7.0.xml#_917f49e9-bbf2-40a3-848a-2c3aea0c2c0d" id="_ffdf023d-f100-428c-8c7f-8b247c1e2a5c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">6</xref>.</li></ol></callout><callout id="_1faa5845-8caa-486a-a121-905b3b40a921"><callout-type info-type="info"/><title id="_96f4a992-1f9a-4631-905b-bc3eff442895">Clear opening width</title><p>An 820 mm clear opening width, for a single swinging door, can generally be achieved using an 870 mm door leaf.</p></callout><callout id="_05a20c19-8119-4f3a-9397-d2534c3f008c"><callout-type info-type="info"/><title id="_4695af2c-b8e4-4b8f-be86-2bedda271f75">Split level designs</title><p>The requirements of 3.1 do not prevent the use of split levels within the dwelling, including on the ground or entrance level. However, where a split level is used in the path of travel to one or more of the doors listed in the Application, those doors will still need to comply with 3.1.</p></callout></clause>